---
description: Use this rule only for code reviews, against the "main" branch on Github
globs:
alwaysApply: false
---

- Compare current branch against `main`.
- If currently on `main`, ask for the right branch and then switch to it.
- Ask questions on the purpose of the pull request.
- Do not install new packages or update existing packages without asking. Explain the benefits of such installation/updates to the developer/reviewer.

- Check for possible memory leaks, with watchers, setTimeout or setInterval.
- Discourage use of console statements.
- Check for more efficient use of regular expressions, if applicable.
- Check if some code can be moved into a helper or util for future use. Ensure DRY.
- Check for infinite loops for recursive functions.
- Check if standard tailwind classes can be used, instead of hard-coded pixel values.
- Check for template errors due to missing imports.
- Suggest stronger protection for cookies.
- Do not import any component, method or type which are auto imported.
- Check for missing implementation of dark mode tailwind classes.
- Suggest jsDoc for complex util or helper functions.

- Create a `.md` file with the branch name to document all the review observations in the **docs** folder, before applying any change.

